        "payload": "tree c78707443a5fa65bdb05d0295516df74e40c7735\nparent 00ac1b963d08f2779d2197edcdb1e76392993378\nauthor josibake <josibake@protonmail.com> 1690121692 +0200\ncommitter josibake <josibake@protonmail.com> 1714992601 +0200\n\ncrypto: add method for applying the taptweak\n\nThe wallet returns an untweaked internal key for taproot outputs. If the\noutput commits to a tree of scripts, this key needs to be tweaked with\nthe merkle root. Even if the output does not commit to a tree of\nscripts, BIP341/342 recommend commiting to a hash of the public key.\n\nPreviously, this logic for applying the taptweak was implemented in the\n::SignSchnorr method.\n\nMove this logic to its own method, ::ApplyTapTweak and refactor\n::SignSchnorr to use this new method.\n\nThe motivation is to be able to use the ::ApplyTapTweak logic outside of\nsigning, e.g. in silent payments when retreiving the private key before\nECDH.\n\nNote: while this is mostly a move-only commit, it is not strictly a\nrefactor. If signing with the merkle_root passed as an argument,\n::SignSchnorr will now require two calls to `secp256k1_keypair_create`.\nWhile this is not a big difference, its also not negligible.\n",
